{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-amp-js","path":"/git-refresh/amp/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Konstantin","author":"Konstantin","siteUrl":"https://konstantin.io"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"e245a6a0-3c96-54d2-9af8-300f6bcf6629","excerpt":"Imagine that you made some commits for which you would like to update the time or a date.(so that you would keep only the chronological order) Now if you were…","html":"<p>Imagine that you made some commits for which you would like to update the time or a date.(so that you would keep only the chronological order)</p>\n<p>Now if you were to do it on the latest commit, you can just run:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">GIT_COMMITTER_DATE<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">date</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\"</span> <span class=\"token function\">git</span> commit --amend --no-edit --date <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">date</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>and that would update the date of the last commit, so you can then <code class=\"language-text\">push</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">push force</code> it.</p>\n<h2 id=\"multiple-commits\"><a href=\"#multiple-commits\" aria-label=\"multiple commits permalink\" class=\"header-anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Multiple commits</h2>\n<p>To perform this action in bulk mode you can just run:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> rebase HEAD~<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>number of commits<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> --ignore-date</code></pre></div>\n<p>You can also create a shortcut in your <code class=\"language-text\">~/.gitconfig</code> like so:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>alias<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n  refresh <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"!f() { git rebase HEAD~<span class=\"token variable\">$1</span> --ignore-date; }; f\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>where the parameter would be number of commits starting from <code class=\"language-text\">HEAD</code> to update, i.e.:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> refresh 6</code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Refresh commit date","tags":["git","commit","date"],"date":"2019-01-01T00:00:00.000Z"},"fields":{"slug":"/git-refresh/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/git-refresh/","previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/gatsby-github/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Running «Gatsby.js» blog with github pages","tags":["gatsby","git","github","blog"],"published":true,"slug":null,"cover_image":null},"fileAbsolutePath":"/Users/gk/projects/gko.github.io/src/posts/gatsby-github.md"},"filename":"git-refresh.md"}},"staticQueryHashes":["983108779"]}